"""
# Primitive API Canary Spec — Wrapper-Type Shape Changes

**Feature IDs:** fix-primitive-api-suppressions
**Category:** Tooling
**Difficulty:** 2/5
**Status:** In Progress
**Requirements:** N/A
**Plan:** N/A
**Design:** N/A
**Research:** N/A
**Artifacts:** N/A

## Overview

Canary specs that lock in specific public functions will use proper wrapper
types instead of bare primitives after Teams D and B fix their suppressions
(Phase 1).

NOTE: These specs verify that the *wrapper-typed call compiles correctly*.
They cannot directly assert the absence of bare `i64`/`i32` in a signature —
that is a grep gate at phase 7-verify.  The specs WILL FAIL until the
relevant team lands the wrapper-type refactor.

Canary targets (from state.md Pre-Pass Types table, Team D scope):
1. `Trace32Client.trace_capture(duration_ms: i32)` → `DurationMs` wrapper
   File: `src/app/debug/remote/protocol/trace32.spl`
2. `backend_shell_tuple(command: text) -> (text, text, i64)` → `ExitCode` in return
   File: `src/compiler/70.backend/backend/io_compat.spl`
3. `is_valid_handle(handle: i64) -> bool` → `Handle` wrapper
   File: `src/app/io/sffi_common.spl`
"""

use std.sspec.*
use types.{DurationMs, Handle, ExitCode}


# ============================================================================
# Canary 1: Trace32Client.trace_capture — DurationMs wrapper
# ============================================================================

describe "AC-2/AC-4 canary: Trace32Client.trace_capture uses DurationMs":
    """
    ## Team D: trace32.spl trace_capture

    After Team D fixes `src/app/debug/remote/protocol/trace32.spl`, the
    `trace_capture` method must accept a `DurationMs` wrapper instead of a
    bare `i32`.  This spec WILL FAIL until Team D replaces
    `duration_ms: i32` with `duration_ms: DurationMs`.
    """

    it "AC-2: trace_capture accepts DurationMs wrapper (not bare i32)":
        # Arrange: wrap the duration in the canonical type
        val duration = DurationMs(value: 100)
        # Act: call via the typed wrapper — this call will fail to compile
        # until the signature is updated to accept DurationMs.
        val client = Trace32Client.connect_default()
        val result = client.trace_capture(duration_ms: duration)
        # Assert: result is Ok (or Err, either is fine — just that it compiles)
        expect(result.is_ok() or result.is_err()).to_equal(true)


# ============================================================================
# Canary 2: backend_shell_tuple — ExitCode in return tuple
# ============================================================================

describe "AC-3 canary: backend_shell_tuple returns ExitCode":
    """
    ## Team D: io_compat.spl backend_shell_tuple

    After Team D fixes `src/compiler/70.backend/backend/io_compat.spl`, the
    return type `(text, text, i64)` must change so the exit-code slot is
    `ExitCode` instead of bare `i64`.  This spec WILL FAIL until Team D
    updates the return tuple type.
    """

    it "AC-3: backend_shell_tuple exit-code slot is ExitCode wrapper":
        # Act: call the function
        val result = backend_shell_tuple("echo hello")
        val exit_code = result.2
        # Assert: exit_code has a .value field — only true if it is ExitCode
        expect(exit_code.value).to_equal(0)


# ============================================================================
# Canary 3: is_valid_handle — Handle wrapper
# ============================================================================

describe "AC-4 canary: sffi_common.is_valid_handle uses Handle":
    """
    ## Team D: sffi_common.spl is_valid_handle

    After Team D fixes `src/app/io/sffi_common.spl`, the function
    `is_valid_handle` must accept a `Handle` wrapper instead of bare `i64`.
    This spec WILL FAIL until Team D replaces `handle: i64` with
    `handle: Handle`.
    """

    it "AC-4: is_valid_handle accepts Handle wrapper (not bare i64)":
        # Arrange: wrap an invalid handle sentinel value
        val h = Handle(value: -1)
        # Act: call with wrapper type — fails to compile until sig updated
        val valid = is_valid_handle(handle: h)
        # Assert: -1 sentinel is not a valid handle
        expect(valid).to_equal(false)
